TY  - JOUR
TI  - Constraints Often Overlooked in Analyses of Simultaneous Equation Models
AU  - Zellner, Arnold
AB  - [In this paper bounds on the values of parameters of simultaneous equation models, implied by usual specifying assumptions, are derived and discussed. It is pointed out that such bounds can be estimated consistently and are formally analogous to those encountered in the classical errors-in-the-variables model.]
